--------------------------------------------------------------
A NYFW Postmortem, DOGE v. New Jersey, Remnick=E2=80=99s Reflections
--------------------------------------------------------------

Welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon bundle of Puck=E2=80=99s =
freshest reporting.

=C2=A0

First up today, Kim Masters makes her Puck debut with a riveting investigat=
ion into the return of Brett Ratner, the pseudo-canceled filmmaker who rece=
ntly resurfaced at Mar-a-Lago (and the White House) to direct a documentary=
 about first lady Melania Trump. While Amazon=E2=80=99s decision to fork ov=
er $40 million to license the film made headlines, the
rehabilitation of Ratner is perhaps most illustrative of these changing tim=
es=E2=80=A6

Plus, below the fold: John Ourand chronicles the rekindled post-Super Bowl =
ESPN-NFL media rights negotiations. Lauren Sherman dissects Calvin Klein=E2=
=80=99s Fashion Week boomerang after a seven-year hiatus. And Abby Livingst=
on gets on the horn with New Jersey A.G. Matthew J.
Platkin to discuss the Democratic attorneys general striking back at DOGE.=
=C2=A0

Meanwhile, on the pods: Legendary New Yorker editor David Remnick joins Dyl=
an Byers on The Grill Room to reflect on the magazine=E2=80=99s centennial =
and its less predictable future. On The Town, Matt Belloni and Lucas Shaw m=
